results.name: Number of 7-regular graphs (septic graphs) on 2n vertices.
comment: Because the triangle A051031 is symmetric, a(n) is also the number of (2n-8)-regular graphs on 2n vertices.
link: Jason Kimberley, Index of sequences counting not necessarily connected k-regular simple graphs with girth at least g
M. Meringer, Fast generation of regular graphs and construction of cages, J. Graph Theory 30 (2) (1999) 137-146.
Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, Septic Graph

xref: 7-regular simple graphs: A014377 (connected), A165877 (disconnected), this sequence (not necessarily connected).

Regular graphs A005176 (any degree), A051031 (triangular array), chosen degrees: A000012 (k=0), A059841 (k=1), A008483 (k=2), A005638 (k=3), A033301 (k=4), A165626 (k=5), A165627 (k=6), this sequence (k=7), A180260 (k=8).
